4. deeper health system
	4.1. more varied healing items
	4.2. effects of healing items
	4.3. sickness (result of events and 0 happiness + hunger)
5. actual rewards for taking good care of pets
	5.1. Pets find items for player
	5.2. Better Exp Curve per for happiness level (multiplier: 1 for 0 happiness, 2 for 100 happiness. Happiness divided by 100 plus 1)
6. More pet connections
	6.1. Minigames with player pets (increase happiness. Zelda 1, mario bros, arcade games with pets as player avatars)
7. Minigames
	7.1. Rail shooter
	7.2. Fruit gathering (fruit falls from tree, basket catches them, bombs fall too)
	7.3. Minigolf (9 holes)
	7.4. Flappy Bird
	7.5. Autoscroll avoid walls game
8. Big collaborative stuff
	8.1. (Football) tournaments
	8.2. Board game (Mario party)

Project definition of done:
- Every country has a reason to explore it
- Pet interactions should feel meaningful
- Daily rewards should let the player come back without feeling like a live service game
- Either fully delve into the mature elements (gore/sex/mental health/addictions) or keep it child friendly